sql:
SELECT AVG(rating) 
FROM reviews 
WHERE provider_id = (SELECT provider_id FROM providers WHERE provider_name = 'Microgaming');

SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM reviews
WHERE provider_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(popularity_score) AS average_popularity
FROM popular_providers
WHERE feature_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
Average rating per provider refers to the mean value of the ratings given to each provider by users; 
Average rating per user refers to the mean value of the ratings given by each user across all their reviews; 
The month of the review is determined by the 'created_at' timestamp in the 'reviews' table.
